  "title": "Enrichment Programme Trainer(Full Time/Part Time)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Highlights</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Are you a MOE Registered Instructor / Post School Teacher / Ex-Teacher / Tutor?</strong></li>\n  <li><strong>YOUTH workers are welcome.</strong></li>\n  <li><strong>Many Time-Slots Available.</strong></li>\n  <li><strong>Attractive Pay.</strong></li>\n  <li><strong>Then you may be interested in this...</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>Job Responsibility</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Conduct different types of  training programmes/lessons for students in both International and MOE schools (mainly primary and secondary schools) with locations in various parts of Singapore</li>\n  <li>Subjects of teaching include different types of skills depending on personnel expertise</li>\n  <li>Some of the subjects could include the following but not subjected to:-</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>You must be a valid MOE eIRS</strong> (Instructor Registration System) registered or if you're in the midst of applying. *Kindly state this information clearly in your application/ resume*</li>\n  <li>Candidate should preferably have 2 or more years of teaching experience</li>\n  <li>Candidate should be flexible</li>\n  <li>Minimum A Level / Diploma / Higher Nitec or equivalent</li>\n  <li>Self-motivated and keen interest in learning new things</li>\n  <li>Must love to teach and enjoy working with children &amp; teenagers</li>\n  <li>Able to handle MOE classes and students</li>\n  <li>Available on weekdays or weekends between 8am – 5:30pm</li>\n  <li>Fluent in Written and spoken English</li>\n  <li>Only Singaporeans &amp; PR need to apply</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Please include the following information in your resume in doc or pdf format:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Personal particulars.</li>\n  <li>Education background.</li>\n  <li>Work experiences.</li>\n  <li>Valid Registration Slip with MOE (It is a MUST).</li>\n</ul>",
